# BUILD PLAYBOOK — Apply to Every Build & Project

> Single source of truth for engineering, security, cost, and growth standards.
> Distilled from 4 source videos (see "Sources" at bottom). When you ship ANY
> feature in ANY project, check it against the relevant sections below.
> If you learn something new worth keeping, append it here and commit.

This playbook is intentionally stack-agnostic, with concrete notes for our
actual stack: **Supabase + FastAPI + Next.js (web) + SwiftUI (iOS) + RevenueCat/Superwall**.

---

## 1. SECURITY — Never ship an insecure app (Sources 3 & 4)

> "One single line of code could end up leaking your entire database."
> AI scaffolding makes it fast to build but easy to leave gaping holes.
> Every one of these is a "vibe-codable" change — you just have to ask for it.

### 1.1 Authentication
- [ ] Real auth: email + password login, not a fake/client-only gate.
- [ ] Add **Google + Apple Sign In** — faster, higher trust, higher conversion.
- [ ] **Email verification** on signup — without it, anyone can sign up as anyone.
- [ ] **2FA / MFA** available for accounts (at minimum for admin/privileged users).

### 1.2 Authorization & data isolation (Row-Level Security)
- [ ] Users can ONLY read/write **their own** data — never anyone else's.
- [ ] Supabase: **RLS enabled on every table**, with explicit policies. A table
      with RLS off is a public table. Verify with `get_advisors` (security).
- [ ] **Admin checks happen on the SERVER, never the client.** A client-side
      `if (user.isAdmin)` is not security — it's a suggestion.

### 1.3 Rate limiting (anti-abuse / anti-brute-force)
- [ ] Rate-limit every public endpoint: login, **password reset**, signup, OTP,
      and any expensive/AI endpoint.
- [ ] Without it, login + reset endpoints can be brute-forced and bots/spammers
      can scrape or exhaust resources.

### 1.4 Server-side validation
- [ ] Validate EVERY field server-side against what's expected (type, length,
      format, range). Never trust client input.
- [ ] FastAPI: enforce with Pydantic schemas; reject unexpected fields.

### 1.5 Session / token handling
- [ ] **Do NOT store session tokens in `localStorage`** → exposed to XSS.
      Prefer **httpOnly, Secure, SameSite cookies**.
- [ ] Short-lived access tokens + refresh rotation.

### 1.6 Password hygiene
- [ ] Enforce **password rule sets** (length/complexity).
- [ ] Run a **leaked/compromised password check** (e.g. HaveIBeenPwned / Supabase
      leaked-password protection) at signup and reset.

### Security ship-gate (run before any release)
1. RLS on for all tables + policies verified (`get_advisors`).
2. All admin/privileged logic enforced server-side.
3. Rate limiting on auth + sensitive endpoints.
4. Server-side validation on all inputs.
5. Tokens in httpOnly cookies, not localStorage.
6. Email verification + password rules + leaked-password check live.

