## 3. REVENUE & GROWTH — Make the app actually earn (Source 1)

> "5 tips that actually increase app revenue." Bake these into product decisions.

### 3.1 Test subscription pricing
- [ ] A/B test price points (try higher, then lower) to find true willingness to pay.
- [ ] Test **weekly vs monthly** plans — many apps make more on weekly.
- [ ] Run via RevenueCat / Superwall experiments.

### 3.2 Optimize the App Store / store page (ASO)
- [ ] Title, subtitle, description **packed with real searched keywords**.
- [ ] High-quality screenshots that **show how the app works** (not just pretty art).

### 3.3 Cancellation save-offer
- [ ] When a user tries to cancel, show **one screen, one offer** (e.g. 50% off)
      before they leave. Set up with RevenueCat / Superwall.

### 3.4 Lifecycle push (day 3)
- [ ] By day 3 users are in or out. Send a push with a **discounted price** to
      convert fence-sitters.

### 3.5 Onboarding → "wow moment"
- [ ] Get users to the value/"wow" moment **before** asking them to sign up or pay.
      This can lift conversion dramatically (~+60% cited).

### Growth ship-gate (for monetized apps)
1. Pricing experiment running (weekly vs monthly tested).
2. Store listing keyword-optimized with how-it-works screenshots.
3. Cancellation save-offer live.
4. Day-3 (and other lifecycle) push configured.
5. Onboarding delivers value before the paywall.

